SIMPLE: oblivious
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Oblivious
<hw>Ob*liv"i*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>obliviosus</ets>: cf. F. <ets>oblivieux</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Promoting oblivion; causing forgetfulness.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>oblivious</xex> pool.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>She lay in deep, <qex>oblivious</qex> slumber.</q>
<rj><qau>Longfellow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Evincing oblivion; forgetful.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Through are both weak in body and <qex>oblivious</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Latimer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Obliv"i*ous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Ob*liv"i*ous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>
<rj><au>Foxe.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>obliviousness</ent>⟦br⟧
